cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.IT 

This paper deals with network disruptions and monitoring of delay and routing patterns between colocation facilities and Internet eXchange Points (IXPs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses anomaly detection techniques, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with monitoring and analyzing data, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with the impact of outages on metropolitan-level networks, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of traceroute data, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
